data.text:
Kevin James is getting ready to create the next film for every one to hate and Rosario Dawson and Leslie Bibb are all aboard as The Zookeeper gets ready to shoot in late summer in Boston with MGM set to release the film on July 23, 2010.

James just scored a massive success with Paul Blart: Mall Cop, which suffered the wrath of many critics (self included), but remains the fifth highest grossing film of the year so far with over $146 million domestically.

The Zookeeper is a live-action romantic comedy centers on zoo animals trying to teach the keeper (James) their methods of dating and mating to help him win back the woman of his dreams. Frank Coraci (Click) is directing from a screenplay by Jay Scherick and David Ronn, Kevin James, Rock Reuben and Nick Bakay.
